<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1289">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 840.48/833</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to <gloss type="to">the
                                    President</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-16">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 16, 1914</hi>.</date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 19, 11 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>21. <hi rend="smallcaps">The President, Washington</hi>: In two weeks the
                            civil population of Belgium, already in misery, will face starvation. In
                            view of this fact, and at the request of the relief committee, I venture
                            to call your attention to my telegram to the Department dated 16th
                            October in the conviction that your great heart will find some way by
                            which America may help to provide food for these hungry ones in the dark
                            days of the terrible winter that is coming on.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WB1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitlock</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>